  "prompt": "I'm new to Quora. What does it mean when someone says they are following me?",
  "response": "When someone on Quora says they are following you, it means they've chosen to see your activity on their Quora feed. Here's a breakdown of what that entails:\n\n*   **Seeing your content:** Followers will see your answers, questions, posts in spaces, and upvotes in their personalized feed. This helps them discover content related to your expertise or interests.\n\n*   **Staying updated:** They'll get notifications (depending on their notification settings) about your new activity. This way, they can stay up-to-date with your contributions to the Quora community.\n\n*   **Showing appreciation/interest:** Following someone is a way of signaling that you find their contributions valuable or interesting. It's like a virtual \"I like what you have to say.\"\n\n*   **Building a connection:** While not a direct message, following can lead to further interaction. They might comment on your answers, upvote your content, or even ask you questions directly.\n\nIn short, being followed on Quora is a good thing! It means you're creating content that resonates with others.\n",
